    "description": "<p data-start=\"478\" data-end=\"814\">Indoors or in dungeons, a Halfling can attempt to hide in deep shadows or cover, but with less success than in natural environments. If sufficient shadows or concealment exist, they have a 33% chance to remain unseen (rolled secretly by the DM). If there is no available cover, the Halfling cannot hide at all.</p><p data-start=\"816\" data-end=\"993\" data-is-last-node=\"\">A bright light, such as a magical light source that eliminates shadows, prevents hiding. A Halfling cannot use this ability while carrying a light source themselves.</p>",
